com.samskivert.util
Class IntIntMap

java.lang.Object
  com.samskivert.util.IntIntMap
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class IntIntMap
extends Object
implements Serializable

An int int map is like an int map, but with integers as values as well as keys. Be careful: get(int) and remove(int) return -1 to indicate that no previous mapping existed. Use getOrElse(int, int) and removeOrElse(int, int) to use a different "default" value.
